===========================
!BoardList 1.02 (04 Jan 97)
© Matthew Page
===========================

 * What it does:

   Allows BBS users to access a database of BBS' online

   The menus are controlled by the cursor keys, but if any of your users have difficulties
   (i.e Hearsay II, doesn't send the correct codes), then they can use: 8=up, 2=down, 4=left, 6=right


 * Instalation:

   Run the door in the usual way:
 
   ArmBBS: door `1 75 <ArmBBS$Dir>.Doors.!BoardList`

   ArcBBS: OSCLI "WimpTask <ArcBBS$Dir>.Doors.!BoardList"
           DOOR 75

   
   Inside the !BoardList directory there is a file called "Config", this file must contain
   the door number (i.e 75), and if you are using ArmBBS or not.

